INSERT INTO `lesson` (`id`, `title`, `duration`, `course_id`, `section_id`, `video_type`, `cloud_video_id`, `video_url`, `date_added`, `last_modified`, `lesson_type`, `attachment`, `attachment_type`, `caption`, `summary`, `is_free`, `order`, `quiz_attempt`, `video_type_for_mobile_application`, `video_url_for_mobile_application`, `duration_for_mobile_application`) VALUES ('1', 'Assessment', '0:00:00', '1', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1697900400', '1698159600', 'quiz', '{\"total_marks\":\"5\"}', 'json', NULL, 'React is quite the buzzword in the industry these days. As of now, React is the most popular front-end technology that more and more companies are using, and if you are preparing for a job interview, this is ReactJS interview questions tutorial is just the right one for you. Here&#039;s a comprehensive list of all the common ReactJS interview questions from basic to advanced levels that are frequently asked in interviews. ', '0', '1', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL), ('2', 'Chapter-1. What is React?', '00:09:33', '1', '1', 'google_drive', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NhlRnKNHHuBosnM_IJpeaCRgkhX6fZE3/view?usp=sharing', '1697900400', '1697986800', 'video', '', 'url', NULL, '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;&quot;&gt;You will gain relevant experience as soon as the first section. Time is precious. And I want to make sure that youll never feel like youre wasting it in this course. So in a matter of minutes, you will be writing React code in the first section, with a fully completed app by the end of it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '1', '2', '0', 'html5', 'https://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/video/basics/devstories.webm', '00:01:10'), ('3', 'Chapter-2. React Hello world', '00:04:53', '1', '1', 'google_drive', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1VSbeKoEFVvIrNGH2UywhO5A7AxtMPKK6/view?usp=sharing', '1697900400', '1697986800', 'video', '', 'url', NULL, '&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(45, 47, 49); font-family: &quot;Udemy Sans&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Roboto, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;;&quot;&gt;discovering all the layers that are in between the supplies that support the React app, and the browser which displays the React app.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '0', '4', '0', 'html5', 'https://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/video/basics/devstories.webm', '00:01:10'), ('4', 'Chapter 3. Correct folder structure ', '00:05:34', '1', '1', 'google_drive', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1smBmI6z2a34_3zYuTwxVGPaz-ZqHUtkD/view?usp=sharing', '1697900400', '1697986800', 'video', '', 'url', NULL, '&lt;p style=&quot;margin: 1rem 0px 0px; color: var(--theme-text-light); font-family: &quot;IBM Plex Sans&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Before I jump into the different folder structures I want to mention one thing. All of these folder structures will only be dealing with the files/folders inside the &lt;code style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.25em; text-shadow: none; color: var(--theme-text); background: var(--theme-code-inline-bg); border-radius: 0.25em;&quot;&gt;src&lt;/code&gt; folder. Outside the &lt;code style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.25em; text-shadow: none; color: var(--theme-text); background: var(--theme-code-inline-bg); border-radius: 0.25em;&quot;&gt;src&lt;/code&gt; folder your files will be very project dependent so there is no good universal structure to apply since it will depend heavily on your project and the libraries you use.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;simple-folder-structure&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 4rem; margin-bottom: 1.38rem; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.3; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 40ch; font-size: clamp(2.074rem, 1.707rem + 0.9175vw, 2.441rem); color: rgb(31, 41, 55); font-family: &quot;IBM Plex Sans&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Simple Folder Structure&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;responsive-img&quot; style=&quot;margin: 1rem 0px 0px; color: var(--theme-text-light); display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; gap: 2em; font-family: &quot;IBM Plex Sans&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://blog.webdevsimplified.com/articleAssets/2022-07/react-folder-structure/beginner.png&quot; alt=&quot;Simple Folder Structure&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; overflow: hidden;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;margin-top: 1rem; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; color: var(--theme-text-light); font-family: &quot;IBM Plex Sans&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;When you first run &lt;code style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.25em; text-shadow: none; color: var(--theme-text); background: var(--theme-code-inline-bg); border-radius: 0.25em;&quot;&gt;create-react-app&lt;/code&gt; there are no folders inside the &lt;code style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.25em; text-shadow: none; color: var(--theme-text); background: var(--theme-code-inline-bg); border-radius: 0.25em;&quot;&gt;src&lt;/code&gt; folder and for most people the first 2 folders they create are a &lt;code style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.25em; text-shadow: none; color: var(--theme-text); background: var(--theme-code-inline-bg); border-radius: 0.25em;&quot;&gt;components&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0.1em 0.25em; text-shadow: none; color: var(--theme-text); background: var(--theme-code-inline-bg); border-radius: 0.25em;&quot;&gt;hooks&lt;/code&gt; folder. Now this is obviously a really simple folder structure but for smaller projects with less than 10-15 components this is honestly not a bad approach.&lt;/p&gt;', '0', '6', '0', 'html5', 'https://www.html5rocks.com/en/tutorials/video/basics/devstories.webm', '00:01:10'), ('5', 'Assessment', '0:02:00', '1', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, '1697900400', '1697986800', 'quiz', '{\"total_marks\":\"2\"}', 'json', NULL, 'for test', '0', '13', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL), ('6', 'Chapter-4. ReactJS Components', '00:04:58', '1', '1', 'google_drive', NULL, 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/1qZ4m5QR16g9dsoojuH9QMtKJH8ExJMmZ/view?usp=sharing', '1697900400', '1697986800', 'video', '', 'url', NULL, '&lt;h3 style=&quot;margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 18.72px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(39, 50, 57); letter-spacing: 0.162px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 18.72px; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;What is a ReactJS Component?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(39, 50, 57); letter-spacing: 0.162px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;A &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;Component&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt; is one of the core building blocks of React. In other words, we can say that every application you will develop in React will be made up of pieces called components. Components make the task of building UIs much easier. You can see a UI broken down into multiple individual pieces called components and work on them independently and merge them all in a parent component which will be your final UI. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;GFG_AD_gfg_mobile_336x280&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(39, 50, 57); letter-spacing: 0.162px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(39, 50, 57); letter-spacing: 0.162px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;You can see in the below image we have broken down the UI of GeeksforGeekss homepage into individual components. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 17px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(39, 50, 57); letter-spacing: 0.162px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1).jpg&quot; alt=&quot;gfgdrawio-(1)&quot; width=&quot;943&quot; height=&quot;418&quot; srcset=&quot;https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1).jpg 943w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1)-100.jpg 100w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1)-200.jpg 200w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1)-300.jpg 300w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1)-660.jpg 660w,https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/uploads/20230804155419/gfgdrawio-(1)-768.jpg 768w&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0px auto 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; max-widt